race.comment: TRINITY'S D'ORO (8) won by a space here this grade and distance and then led them up again at Yarra Valley and just missed. Carries just a kilo more since the win here and he can bounce back. PRESTIGE GEOFFREY (7) was heading in the right direction before a plain run at Echuca. He's placed in a Cranbourne jumpout since and won his only second-up start. Maps for a soft run and the blinkers are applied for the first time. Not to be underestimated. There will be trust required with POWERBOUND (1), but he has the ability and will be better for the run at Camperdown. Has the rail and 1.5kg claim and he's been racing all campaign in much stronger. CHILLI REAPER (6) missed a whisker at Donald and then was slow to recover when disappointing as a $6 favourite at Echuca. Has a low gate and the blinkers on for the first time. Can get back on track. EMMCEE (11) showed more like his best at Stawell the latest and on that effort deserves consideration.
